  <title>Cyber Security Basics</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="./cyber.css">
</head>
<body>

  
  <header>
    <div class="logo-title">
      <img src="/logo/cyber.jpg" alt="Cybersecurity Logo" class="logo">
      <h1>Cyber Security Basics</h1>
    </div>
    <p class="tagline">Stay safe online – learn how to protect your data and devices.</p>
  </header>

 
  <section class="intro">
    <h2>🔒 What is Cybersecurity?</h2>
    <p>Cybersecurity is the practice of defending computers, mobile devices, servers, networks, 
       and data from malicious attacks. It plays a crucial role in protecting both individuals 
       and organizations from financial loss, data breaches, and identity theft.</p>
  </section>

  
  <section class="importance">
    <h2>🌍 Why Cybersecurity is Important</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Protects your personal information from hackers.</li>
      <li>Keeps devices safe from viruses and malware.</li>
      <li>Prevents financial fraud and identity theft.</li>
      <li>Ensures company and government data security.</li>
      <li>Helps build trust in digital services and e-commerce.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

 
  <section class="threats">
    <h2>⚠️ Common Cyber Threats</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <img src="/logo/phishing.png" alt="Phishing Email Example">
        <h3>Phishing</h3>
        <p>Fake emails or websites designed to steal personal information, such as passwords and banking details.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <img src="/logo/malware.png" alt="Malware Attack">
        <h3>Malware</h3>
        <p>Malicious software like viruses, worms, and spyware that can damage your system or steal data.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <img src="/logo/ransomeware.png" alt="Ransomware Attack">
        <h3>Ransomware</h3>
        <p>Hackers lock your files and demand payment to unlock them. One of the fastest-growing threats.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <img src="/logo/hacking.png" alt="Hacking">
        <h3>Hacking</h3>
        <p>Unauthorized access to accounts, social media, or entire computer systems to steal or misuse information.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  
  <section class="tips">
    <h2>🛡️ Cyber Safety Tips</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Use strong and unique passwords (avoid “12345” or names).</li>
      <li>Don’t click on suspicious links or attachments.</li>
      <li>Keep software, apps, and antivirus up to date.</li>
      <li>Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) wherever possible.</li>
      <li>Be careful on public Wi-Fi – use VPN for safety.</li>
      <li>Regularly back up your important files.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

 
  <section class="career">
    <h2>💼 Careers in Cybersecurity</h2>
    <p>Cybersecurity is one of the fastest-growing industries, with demand for skilled professionals worldwide. Popular roles include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Security Analyst:</strong> Monitors systems for suspicious activities.</li>
      <li><strong>Ethical Hacker:</strong> Tests systems to find weaknesses before attackers do.</li>
      <li><strong>SOC Analyst:</strong> Works in a Security Operations Center to detect threats in real-time.</li>
      <li><strong>Network Security Engineer:</strong> Designs and maintains secure networks.</li>
      <li><strong>Incident Responder:</strong> Responds to and mitigates cyberattacks.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  
